.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
.\" change 51
It is now possible to set pager and editor preferences in your
\fI\.aegisrc\fP file.  See \fIaeuconf\fP(5) for more information.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
.\" change 50
A bug in \fIaepatch \-receive\fP has been fixed, where it would sometimes
misapply a patch. The search used to determine the patch position (when
it needs to be offset) has been improved.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
.\" change 37
The \fIaedist\fP(1) and \fIaepatch\fP(1) commands now accept \-delta
and \-delta-date options.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
.\" change 35, 53
The \fIintegrate_q.sh\fP shell script has been replaced by the
\fIaeintegratq\fP(1) Perl script.  It can now lots more useful things.
See \fIaeintegratq\fP(1) for more information.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
.\" change 29
A bug has been fixed in the date parsing code (used by the \-delta-date option).
There was the potential to mis-calculate dates after February 2000.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
.\" change 29
A bug has been fixed in \fIaepatch \-receive\fP, where it sometimes
complain of "no uudecode data in file", for files which did not require
uudecoding.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
.\" change 20
There are more change-specific substitutions available.
See \fI${change ...} \fP within \fIaesub\fP(5) for more information.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
.\" change 17
The \fIaepatch\fP(1) command now understands ordinary diff listings,
in addition to the context and unified differences it already understood.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
.\" change 15, 16, 18, 19, 21, 22, 23, 27, 28
There is a new \fIaeannotate\fP(1) command, used to produce annotated
source file listings.  See \fIaeannotate\fP(1) for more information.
